<p>April 21: Digital Humanities Lab (Guest: Nick Budak, Developer at the Center for Digital Humanities, Princeton)
Pre-Lab assignment:
Visit The First Family of Radio site and listen to FDR‚Äôs fireside chat on ‚ÄúThe WPA and Social Security,‚Äù from April 28, 1935
Check out these web platforms that allow you to create sounds for your digital projects.
For free podcast hosting, Spotify has a service called Anchor. Once your podcast is hosted with them, you can easily embed it into your site with HTML embed code.
For studio-level audio creation and manipulation, Spotify has a service called Soundtrap. If you‚Äôre interested, I can get us a free trial for 30 days with my Princeton email.
For music composition and annotation (with sheet music), there‚Äôs a free online service called Flat.io.
Post to our canvas discussion
In-class presentation and Q&amp;A with Nick Budak, Developer at the Center for Digital Humanities, Princeton</p>

